column2: Water temp 64 degrees.  Has been windy.  Insect casts.
Water 74 degrees- clear and calm.  Modest algae.
Water 76 degrees. 1" rain in week.  Less algae.
Water 75 degrees.  Very dry- no rain for 3 weeks.  Windy.
Water 75 degrees- hazy. Prolonged drought.  Algae bloom last week.
Water 72 degrees.  1" rain. air 68 degrees.  Water clearing.
Water 73 degrees- air 80 degrees.  Clear- NW wind at 10+ mph.
Warm- humid- high overcast- wind S-SW 10-15- water 73 deg. F- 3 loons- 1 cormorant- 2 black ducks.
Clear to partly cloudy - cool- approx. 60 deg.  Water 68 deg. wind NW 10-15 mph- water in shallows quite clear.
Clear to partly cloudy.  Wind NW 5-10 mph- 69 deg. F- water 73 deg. F- 20' deep.  Day before cool + rainy- following hot windy days.
Clear- W-NW 5-10 mph- 67 deg. F- water 74 deg.  No rain for week but 6 3/4" since last reading - lake up +4-6" - now normal.
2 days after 2" rain - cold N wind - vegetation deteriorating - cool- sunny - water 70 degrees F.
78 deg. F- wind NW 5 mph- water 76 deg. F.  Weed deterioration - algae bloom all week - near shore 3'.
Bad green-brown bloom moved in on wind - secchi 2' at pier.  Wind NW at 5 mph.  Clear- cool - geese migrating- lake 62 deg. F.
Water 58 deg. F- mostly overcast- 57 deg. F- wind light - north trees at peak.  Some surface algae along shore.
Water 66 degrees F. NW wind 5-10 mph. No loon. Very dry conditions. Water bluish brown.
Clear. water 70 degrees F.- air 65 degrees F. W wind 5 mph. in shore water very clear. 1.5" rain. 1 eagle- loon May be nesting.
Water 73 degrees F- air 70 degrees F. ESE wind 5-10 mph. partly to mostly cloudy. 1 blue heron. 7" rain since last report.
Water 76 degrees- ENE wind 5 mph. clear to partly cloudy. 2.8" rain since last reading. 6 days of 75 to 80 degrees temperatures.
Water 75 degrees- air 70 degrees. S wind 10-12 mph. overcast. water plants very good condition. a few floating weeds.
Water 76 degrees F.- air 76 degrees F. clear- WSW wind 5-8 mph. clear. 2 loons at site. water plants fading- modest suspended bloom.
Water 58 degrees F.- air 58 degrees F. clear- WNW wind 5-10 mph. wind and rain for 3 days. several gulls- 1 loon. green soup at shore- heavy in-shore bloom.
The air temperature is 74 degrees- partly overcast- storm previous night- warm previous week- and some surface alga.
Lake conditions and weather are beautiful.
The air temperature is 70 degrees- reading after two weeks of hot weather- water clear for late July- and stained but little suspended algae.
The air temperature is 60 degrees- light northwest wind- partly cloudy- Merlin flying- much suspended algae- looks like green colonial- and near surface of lake the temperature had been 87 degrees.
Had been very cold over the weekend- some snow- wind south-southwest at 15 mph and becoming high overcast- the aquatic plants are still okay.
Warm and clear weather- first warm day in weeks. Almost calm- 1 loon
air 70 F- high thin overcast. Wind 15-20 mph south. Couldn't hold over site.
Clear. SE winds at 5 mph. Loon pair and 1/2 grown juvenile. 18 of 20 days above normal temperature.
High- thin overcast. SW winds at 10 mph. 74 deg F. 3 weeks of suspended bloom following 2 very windy storms. Juvenile loon.
Sunny- calm. Vegetation still ok. Recovering from bloom. Immature loon- blue heron- several gulls
Mostly overcast- 5-10 mph wind NW- 2" rain previous day. 10 days below normal temp. 50 deg F air temp. Color at peak.
clear-s.e. wind 5- 1 loon- 2 inch rain previous days
cool with high overcast- wind light-2 adult and 2
high overcast-wind light-2 inch rain previous week
clear and calm after 2 weeks of cold-wet- windy

column1: weather- 2 immature loons- color not yet developed much

column2: poor observing conditions-middle overcast- air 56 degrees- wind NE at 10
partly cloudy-wind west at 10-cool dry weather 62 degrees-loon pair but no chicks
high thin overcast-wind west at 5- prolonged dry spell with no surface inflow from streams for many days- three loons
cool- wind SE at 8-10- partly cloudy- several days with ave. temp 10 or more degrees below normal- extremely dry- soft maples turning color- 2 loons
clear- 60 degrees- wind SW at 5- above normal temperatures for 4 weeks- peak of fall color- persistent moderate algal bloom along shore for most of Sept. and Oct.
loon nesting-large flock of geese heading north-clear and calm-70-75 degrees
partly overcast- 75 degrees- wind SE 5-8 mph- loon pair and chick at Hardt Bay- 3 inch rain during week
sunny- 85 degrees- wind SW 10-15- near record warm weather- dry-  water excellent- waves make sampling difficult
70 degrees- clear- wind SW 5-10- 2 loons- 1 eagle
Clear - wind NW 5-10 mph.  1/2" rain broke profound drought- lake 6" lower than normal.
Partly cloudy - wind NW 5-10 mph.  2 1/2 " rain previous night.  Moderate algal bloom.  Bottom temp. 63.5 F.
Cold wet week.  Temp. 50s.  SW 5-8 mph.  Heavy surface algae on east shore.  Water rather murky for fall.
clear and warm- wind west at 10- 1 eagle - one loon pair
clear and pleasant- light wind- air about 70- has been cool with 1.5 inches rain
partly cloudy to overcast- wind s sw 5-10- essential no rain in past 4 weeks- no surface stream input to lake since May- highs in 80's and lows about 60 for last 3 weeks
air temp 71 degres- about 12 inches of rain in past 2 weeks
Put out loon platform- 2 loons on the lake near the island.
clear-calm-very dry- no stream input to lake- lake low 3"- frost over night- air 58 degrees
Loons on platform- 2 eggs present- no black flies
clear/partly cloudy-wind west 3-5-1" rain for week- air 70 degrees
1" rain-5+ " deficit-very cool for several days- water temp going down-wind south at 10- air 73 degrees-drifted off site - could not get deep water oxygen values
less than 1/2 inch rain since last observation-clear after warm humid week- wind W 10-12-very clear water with plants still green and healthy- unusual for late summer
Partly cloudy- windy- one loon present.  Macro invertebrates collected included scud- caddisfly larva- mayfly larva- nematode- cyclops.
2.9 inches rain previous night- wind W-NW 5-10- clear- loon call

Four adult loons and one chick present.  Aquatic plants sampled include arum-leaved arrowhead- clasping leaf pondweed- fern pondweed- flatstem pondweed- bushy pondweed- spiral fruited pondweed- water smartweed- coontail- whorled water milfoil- eloda canadensis- needle spike rush and white pond lily.
clear to partly cloudy- wind W-SW 5-10- 2 loon- 1 herring gull
high overcast-light NW wind- 84 degree air temp after cold week-- wind shift to west 8-12 mph
clear to partly cloudy- wind N about 5 mph- warm and clear for several days
clear to partly cloudy-  wind WNW 4-8 mph- warm and pleasant- little rain for 2 weeks-

column1: herring gulls appeared- loon heard- pair of chicks now well grown
